'''''telco''''' is the [[Quenya]] word for "leg".<ref>{{PE|17}}, p. 122</ref> Hence ''[[Telcontar|'''Telco'''ntar]]'' ("Strider").<ref>{{HM|RC}}, "[[The Houses of Healing]]", p. 580</ref>

''Telco'' also refers to the straight 'stem' line that appears in written [[Tengwar]], which can extend above or below the writing line (although in the original system there was a third option, a telco that extended both above and below the line). Combined with the ''[[lúva]]'' ("bow") stroke, it forms the basis of all the standard characters of the [[Fëanorian alphabet]].<ref>{{App|Letters}}</ref>

